                         Financial Services Division

      The Financial Services Division (FSD) is one of three operational
   divisions under the California Corporations Commissioner. FSD is headed
    by an Assistant Commissioner and is responsible for the regulation of
                             four separate laws.

                  The laws under FSD's responsibility are:
     * California Finance Lenders Law
     * California Residential Mortgage Lending Act
     * Check Sellers, Bill Payers and Proraters Law
     * Escrow Law


